Let P = $$\left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   3 &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   9 &amp; 3 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$ and Q = [q<sub>ij</sub>] be two 3 $$ \times $$ 3 matrices such that Q – P<sup>5</sup> = I<sub>3</sub>.  
<br><br>Then  $${{{q_{21}} + {q_{31}}} \over {{q_{32}}}}$$ is equal  to :

questions.solution:
$$P = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   3 &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   9 &amp; 3 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$
<br><br>$${P^2} = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {3 + 3} &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {9 + 9 + 9} &amp; {3 + 3} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$
<br><br>$${P^3} = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {3 + 3 + 3} &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {6.9} &amp; {3 + 3 + 3} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$
<br><br>$${P^n} = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {3n} &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {{{n\left( {n + 1} \right)} \over 2}{3^2}} &amp; {3n} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$
<br><br>$${P^5} = \left[ {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {5.3} &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {15.9} &amp; {5.3} &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right]$$
<br><br>$$Q = {P^5} + {{\rm I}_3}$$
<br><br>$$Q = \left[ {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {15} &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {135} &amp; {15} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right]$$
<br><br>$${{{q_{21}} + {q_{31}}} \over {{q_{32}}}} = {{15 + 135} \over {15}} = 10$$
<br><br>Aliter
<br><br>$$P = \left( {\matrix{
   1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1  \cr 

 } } \right) + \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   3 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   9 &amp; 3 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)$$
<br><br>$$P = {\rm I} + X$$
<br><br>$$X = \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   3 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   9 &amp; 3 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)$$
<br><br>$${X^2} = \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   9 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)$$
<br><br>$${{X_3} = 0}$$
<br>$${{P^5} = {\rm I} + 5X + 10{X^2}}$$
<br>$${Q = {P^5} + {\rm I} = 2{\rm I} + 5X + 10{X^2}}$$
<br><br>$$Q = \left( {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right) + \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {15} &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {15} &amp; {15} &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right) + \left( {\matrix{
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {90} &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 

 } } \right)$$
<br><br>$$ \Rightarrow \,\,Q = \left( {\matrix{
   2 &amp; 0 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {15} &amp; 2 &amp; 0  \cr 
   {135} &amp; {15} &amp; 2  \cr 

 } } \right)$$
